{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780127299910,"sessionID":"ses_18826e0a6ffewJt96BqqZwGoRN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_function_eln2lcoe8bnf_1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F1\",\"dimension\":\"structural\",\"content\":\"deep-improvement skill structure is self-referential on routing: INTINT_SIGNALS/RESOURCE_MAP/RUNTIME_ASSETS determine which sub-documents load\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:97-214\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F2\",\"dimension\":\"architectural\",\"content\":\"Three pluggable seams exist: candidate-source, dispatcher, scorer — Lane C can plug into the scorer seam for skill-benchmark mode\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:275-280\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F3\",\"dimension\":\"structural\",\"content\":\"Lane-aware reference organization under references/ and assets/ — skill-benchmark harness must observe which refs/assets load vs should have loaded\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:81-88\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F4\",\"dimension\":\"distinction\",\"content\":\"sk-doc validates shape/package-structure, not behavioral usefulness — Lane C fills the behavioral gap\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:14-20,.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:46-50\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F5\",\"dimension\":\"distinction\",\"content\":\"system-skill-advisor routes requests externally, does not measure internal skill router accuracy — Lane C operates one layer deeper\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:59-73\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F6\",\"dimension\":\"prior-art\",\"content\":\"Coverage metric from Brown et al. 2024 (LLM Monkeys): coverage = skill-on task success minus skill-off success; scales log-linearly with sampling\",\"source\":\"arxiv.org/abs/2407.21787\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F7\",\"dimension\":\"prior-art\",\"content\":\"Tau-Bench (Berkeley) establishes multi-round agent eval with tool-call trace capture — Lane C can use same trace capture for routing observation\",\"source\":\"arxiv.org/abs/2404.08144\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F8\",\"dimension\":\"prior-art\",\"content\":\"Tool retrieval precision/recall (ToolACE, API-Bank, BMT): routing precision = right refs loaded, routing recall = all relevant refs loaded, argument binding ≈ INTENT_SIGNALS keyword match quality\",\"source\":\"academic synthesis\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F9\",\"dimension\":\"prior-art\",\"content\":\"LLM-as-judge for usefulness scoring with vs without skill context; requires careful prompt engineering to avoid circularity\",\"source\":\"academic synthesis\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F10\",\"dimension\":\"measurement-framework\",\"content\":\"Five candidate scoring dimensions: Routing/Activation Accuracy, Discovery Precision+Recall, Efficiency/Bottlenecks, Usefulness (skill-on vs skill-off ablation), Structural Connectivity (orphan refs, dead router keys)\",\"source\":\"synthesized F1-F9\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F11\",\"dimension\":\"measurement-framework\",\"content\":\"Normalization across skill shapes: fractional scores per skill size, per-dimension z-scores against population, complexity-weighted aggregation\",\"source\":\"synthesized\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"iteration\":1,\"id\":\"F12\",\"dimension\":\"architectural\",\"content\":\"loop-host.cjs --mode=skill-benchmark is the correct entry point following Lane B pattern; dispatcher remains skill-advisor, scorer becomes Lane C benchmark scorer\",\"source\":\".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:277-280\"}","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/